'''Barbara Thomas, Lady Judge''', [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (n<U+00E9>e Barbara Sue Singer;<ref name=fsa>[https://www.fsa.gov.uk/register/indivBasicDetails.do;jsessionid=f6c8127091744e2d98c1bdb6ea5727bf.s6fNml1Ka38InBbv-ArJrwTPoNCNa30Ocybtah0IaNuIahiIbh0IaNfwmxiInxiObk9ynhvybMSHc30Ka2aToi5hch0Na2TSn7bvq70KawTAqQ4InQXQ-BjF8NaOahiRawbMnkrDqRfzqwbMnkrDqRfzqwbynknvrkLOlQzNp65In0__?sid=423484 UK Financial Services Authority]</ref> born 28 December 1946<ref name=debretts>[http://www.debretts.com/people/biographies/browse/j/12560/Barbara%20S%20Judge+JUDGE.aspx Lady Judge, CBE], Debrett's.</ref> in [[New York City]]), known before her second marriage as '''Barbara Singer Thomas''', is an [[United States|American]] [[lawyer]], businesswoman and lobbyist who lives in [[London]] and has [[Multiple citizenship|dual citizenship]].<ref name=cityview>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/7a2baba0-ea82-11e0-b0f5-00144feab49a.html|title=Reformer with a City view|newspaper=Financial Times|last=Maccoby Berglof|first=Annie|date=7 October 2011}}</ref> Lady Judge is Chairman Emeritus of the [[United Kingdom Atomic Energy Authority|UK Atomic Energy Authority]] (UKAEA), Chairman of the [[Pension Protection Fund]], and UK Business Ambassador on behalf of [[UK Trade & Investment]].<ref>[http://www.dwp.gov.uk/previous-administration-news/press-releases/2010/april-2010/dwp066-10-070410.shtml Lady Judge appointed Chair of Pension Protection fund]. DWP. Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref><ref>[http://www.number10.gov.uk/news/press-notices/2010/11/pm-announces-new-business-ambassadors-56764 PM announces new Business Ambassadors]. Number10.gov.uk (2010-11-09). Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref><ref name=chairukaea>[http://www.niauk.org/news/latest-nuclear-news/judge-to-chair-ukaea.html NIA <U+2013> The Nuclear Industry Association <U+2013> Judge to chair UKAEA]. Niauk.org (2004-07-30). Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref>
She is married to Sir [[Paul Judge]] and has a son from her first marriage to Allen L. Thomas, an American lawyer.

==Education and early career==
Barbara Singer's father had a small business. Her mother Marcia Singer was associate dean of students at [[New York Institute of Technology]] until 2011.<ref name=helmsec/><ref name=cityview/><ref>[http://www.nyit.edu/administrative_offices/student_affairs_staff/ Student Affairs Staff], New York Institute of Technology.</ref> Born in [[Manhattan]], Barbara Singer grew up in [[Saddle Rock, New York]].<ref name=helmsec>{{cite newspaper|title=She's now at helm of SEC|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1873&dat=19810316&id=vVAfAAAAIBAJ&sjid=09EEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3626,50651|newspaper=Daytona Beach Morning Journal|last=Nemy|first=Enid|date=16 March 1981}}</ref>

In 1966 she graduated with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in [[History]] from the [[University of Pennsylvania]].<ref name=secrep>[http://www.sec.gov/about/annual_report/1983.pdf 49th Annual Report of th Securities and Exchange Committee] (1983), p.&nbsp;xvi.</ref> In her subsequent studies at [[New York University School of Law]], she specialised in tax law,<ref name=nyu>[http://www.law.nyu.edu/alumni/almo/pastalmos/2009-10ALMOs/ladybarbarathomasjudge/index.htm NYU Law <U+2013> 2009-10 ALMOs: Lady Barbara Thomas Judge (October)]. Law.nyu.edu. Retrieved on 2011-12-11.</ref> finishing with a [[Juris Doctor]] in 1969.<ref name=cv>[http://www.ukti.gov.uk/uktihome/aboutukti/item/123289.html Lady Barbara Thomas Judge <U+2013> Business Ambassador Profile]. Ukti.gov.uk (2011-03-22). Retrieved on 2011-04-13.<br/>[http://www.whartondubai09.com/bio-thomas.html Biography of Lady Barbara Judge]. Whartondubai09.com. Retrieved on 2011-12-11.</ref><ref name=r1/><ref name=secrep/> She won numerous awards for her grades and was an editor of the [[NYU Law Review|New York University Law Review]].<ref name=secrep/><ref name=r1>[http://www.bekaert.com/en/Investors/Datacenter%20and%20downloads/Legal%20publications/~/media/Files/Investors/Corporate%20Governance/Legal%20publications/2007/07%2004%2013%20CV%20ENG%20Lady%20Judgepdf.ashx Lady Judge (formerly known as Barbara S Thomas)]</ref>

At her first employer, Barbara Singer worked as a corporate lawyer. In 1973, she joined ''Kaye, Scholer, Fierman, Hays, and Handler'', where she specialised in corporate law and financial transactions and became a partner in 1978.<ref name=nyu/> At that time she married Allen L. Thomas, a partner at her first firm.<ref name=helmsec/>

==SEC and banking==
In 1980, Barbara Thomas was appointed a member of the [[U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission]] (SEC) in [[Washington, D.C.]] for a five-year term.<ref name=womenmanagers>[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Jk_uzzu36rgC&lpg=PA268&pg=PA268 Judith A. Leavitt, American women managers and administrators:a selective biographical dictionary of twentieth-century leaders in business, education, and government, Greenwood 1985, p268]</ref> As she was the youngest SEC commissioner, this was widely reported and a key stage in her career.<ref name=lincoln>{{cite news|last=Gerth|first=Jeff|date=1 January 1990|title=Some Lincoln investors escape loss in collapse|url=http://www.nytimes.com/1990/01/01/business/some-lincoln-investors-escape-loss-in-collapse.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm}}</ref><ref name=nyu/> In November 1983, after the birth of her son, she resigned to become a director of the British [[merchant bank]] [[Samuel Montagu & Co.]] (now part of [[HSBC Private Bank]]<ref>[http://www.hsbcpb.com/aboutus/our-origins.html Our Origins], HSBC Private Bank.</ref>) and move to [[Hong Kong]] with her husband.<ref name=secrep/><ref name=connected>{{cite newspaper|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-452635/Is-best-connected-woman-Britain.html|title=Is this the best connected woman in Britain?|date=4 May 2007|last=Sands|first=Sarah|newspaper=Daily Mail}}</ref><ref name=friend>{{cite news|url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/news/article-13125878-judge-and-friend-shed-rather-forget.do|title=Judge and friend she'd rather forget|last=Leach|first=Andrew|date=12 September 2004|newspaper=London Evening Standard}}</ref> In 1987 she became senior vice president of Bankers Trust International Banking in New York.<ref name=cv/>

Around that time, Barbara Thomas was also involved with [[Lincoln Savings and Loan Association]] and [[American Continental Corporation]], two companies whose collapse in 1989 would cause a [[Keating Five|major financial scandal]].<ref name=lincoln/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newspaperarchive.com/SiteMap/FreePdfPreview.aspx?img=113642092|newspaper=Kokomo Tribune|title=Money, connections equal power|last=Eskey|first=Kenneth|date=21 November 1989}}</ref><ref>[http://www.leagle.com/xmlResult.aspx?xmldoc=19912164782FSupp1382_11939.xml&docbase=CSLWAR2-1986-2006 In re AMERICAN CONTINENTAL CORPORATION/LINCOLN SAVINGS AND LOAN SECURITIES LITIGATION], 782 F.Supp. 1382 (1991), p. 10f.</ref> Both companies were run by [[Charles Keating]], for whom she lobbied with the SEC in 1988.<ref name=friend/><ref name=lincoln/> Later she was named in a resulting class action suit and settled out of court.<ref name=friend/><ref name=trends/>

==News International and private equity==
In 1993, Barbara Thomas became an executive director of [[Rupert Murdoch]]'s [[News International]], and in 1994 she moved from New York to London with her husband and her son, whom she wanted to raise in England.<ref name=cv/><ref name=trends>{{cite news|newspaper=Trends|lang=nl|title=De lady van Bekaert|url=http://trends.knack.be/economie/nieuws/mensen/de-lady-van-bekaert/article-1194635063313.htm|date=3 May 2007}}</ref><ref name=connected/> Later she worked in the [[private equity]] business in the UK (acquisition of Scotia Haven Food Group and Whitworths Food Group) and founded ''Private Equity Investor plc''.<ref name=cv/>

Thomas was also on the Board of Overseers of the [[Wharton School of Management]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]] and a founding director of the [[Lauder Institute]] of Management at Wharton.<ref name=cv/>

==Nuclear power and pension protection==
After her marriage to Sir Paul Judge, Lady Judge became a non-executive director in 2002, and in 2004 the chair, of the [[UK Atomic Energy Authority]] (UKAEA).<ref name=chairukaea/> After the sale of the UKAEA's decommissioning business to [[Babcock International Group]] in 2009, she was succeeded by [[Roger Cashmore]] in 2010.<ref>[http://www.uk-atomic-energy.org.uk/about_history.html History], United Kingdom Atomic Energy Authority.</ref><ref>[http://www.uk-atomic-energy.org.uk/press10July27.html New chair of United Kingdom Atomic Energy Authority Appointed], United Kingdom Atomic Energy Authority, 27 July 2010.</ref> In the same year she was appointed [[Order of the British Empire|Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) for "services to the Nuclear and Financial Services Industries".<ref>[http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/59446/supplements/7 Viewing Page 7 of Issue 59446]. London-gazette.co.uk (2010-06-12). Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref> In February 2010, she was also appointed to the International Advisory Board for the development of nuclear energy in the [[United Arab Emirates]] (UAE). In February 2011, she led a trade delegation to [[India]] to discuss how British companies could take part in the construction of six giant [[nuclear reactors]] at [[Jaitapur]] on the west coast of the country.<ref>[http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/world/asia/article2920208.ece UK News, World News and Opinion]. The Times. Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref>

Lady Judge is the chairman of the nuclear power plant industry start-up [[Hyperion Power Generation]].

In April 2010, Lady Judge was appointed Chairman of the [[Pension Protection Fund]] (PPF), a position that she took up in July 2010.<ref name=ppf-profile>[http://www.pensionprotectionfund.org.uk/ABOUT-US/THEBOARD/Pages/barbarajudge.aspx Lady Judge CBE]. Pensionprotectionfund.org.uk. Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref> Between 2007 and 2010, Lady Judge was a Public Member of the [[International Ethics Standards Board for Accountants]], a body which develops ethical standards and guidance for use by professional accountants.<ref name=cv/> Additionally, from 2004 until 2007, Lady Judge was Deputy Chairman of the UK Financial Reporting Council which regulates UK corporate governance and accountants.<ref>[http://www.cbs19.tv/Global/story.asp?S=13839363 Lady Barbara Judge: Kazakhstan is Embracing Nuclear Power <U+2013> KYTX CBS 19 Tyler Longview News Weather Sports]. Cbs19.tv. Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref>

Lady Judge is chair of the Energy Institute at [[University College, London]].<ref name=profile>[http://www.worldforesightforum.org/Barbara-Judge/page/5231/ Lady Barbara Judge]. World Foresight Forum. Retrieved on 2011-04-13.<br/>[http://www.sbs.ox.ac.uk/centres/reputation/visitingfellows/Pages/default.aspx Visiting Fellows]. Sbs.ox.ac.uk. Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref> In January 2006, she was appointed by the [[School of Oriental and African Studies]] in London (SOAS) as Chairman of its governing body, and is also Chairman of the advisory board for the London Middle East Institute at SOAS.<ref>[http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/95aa24d8-8c7d-11da-9efb-0000779e2340.html#axzz1EyYnFRR9 / UK <U+2013> Lady Barbara to the helm at SOAS]. Ft.com (2006-01-24). Retrieved on 2011-04-13.</ref> Elsewhere, Lady Judge is a member of the International Board of Overseers of [[Sabanc<U+0131> University]], Istanbul, and a visiting fellow of the [[University of Oxford]] [[Sa<U+00EF>d Business School]], at the Centre for Corporate Reputation.<ref name=profile/>

